        Experiments

        Experiments This section describes the experiments during the analysis

        Principle Component Analysis (PCA)
        Test whether human milk is different from bovine milk in terms of metabolites
        Hierarcical Clustering
        This shows top 50 (ranked by two-sample t-test p-value from lowest to highest) significant metabolites that make bovine milk different from bovine milk. If the metabolite has a match in SECIM library, the name will show on the plot, otherwise it would be an unknown metabolite
        Bar Plot
        This shows top 10 matched metabolites with a significant p-value and with the most positive/negative fold change
        Venn Diagram
        It shows the overlap and difference between the two materials
